						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall of the Veṅkaṭēśa-perumāḷ temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Kōṉēriṉmaikoṇḍāṉ (Vīrarājēndradēva): Year 21, 82nd day = 1227-28 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription dated in the 82nd day of the 21st year of the king records the royal order granting 16 <hi rend="italic">nāḻi</hi> of rice daily for food offerings to god Aruvaraiāttatta-Piḷḷaiyār, set up at Koḻumam by some people (name not clear). </p>						

						</summary>
